In order to get any license under these terms, you must agree to them as both strict obligations and conditions to all your licenses.

2. Copyright License
The licensor grants you a copyright license for the software to do everything you might do with the software that would otherwise infringe the licensor’s copyright in it for any permitted purpose. However, you may only distribute the software according to Distribution License and make changes or new works based on the software according to Changes and New Works License.

3. Patent License
The licensor grants you a patent license for U.S. and foreign patents owned or controlled by the licensor for the software and the use, operation, modification, and distribution of the software according to these terms for any permitted purpose.

4. Distribution License
The licensor grants you an additional copyright license to distribute copies of the software. Your license to distribute covers distributing the software with changes and new works permitted by Changes and New Works License.

5. Changes and New Works License
The licensor grants you an additional copyright license to make changes and new works based on the software for any permitted purpose.

6. Noncommercial Purpose
A noncommercial purpose means any purpose that is not the operation of an organization that has annual gross revenue exceeding $1,000,000 USD before inflation adjustment, or the operation of a for-profit business or organization.

7. Notices
You must ensure that anyone who gets a copy of any part of the software from you also gets a copy of these terms or the URL for them above, as well as copies of any plain-text lines beginning with “Required Notice:” that the licensor provided with the software. For example:

